commit 4c3ecbc8c2a5d015de726cd5d00bb32801f81f36
Author: Francois Rigaut <frigaut@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Aug 25 09:18:08 2015 +1000

    added zernike wfs (the actual one now, e.g.
    http://exep.jpl.nasa.gov/lowfsc/agenda/Ndiaye_Mamadou.pdf )
    wfs.type="zwfs" (which is also the name of the function).
    This was implemented as a user sensor, i.e. I didn't put special
    hooks in multwfs or other location, just use the user_wfs feature
    that calls the routine of the same name as wfs.type
    
    Also added sh+zer.par which is an example parfile.

