      in shwfs_init(). To restore this feature, set optimize_nx=1
    - LLTlaserM2 was not implemented but did not give an error message when
    used. Gotten rid of this structure member. Instead, use wfs.kernel.
    - CHANGE: now displays the WFS pixels (in display) with bytscl, so
      e.g. tip-tilt on a quadcell will not appear so confusing/moving than
      before.
    - ADDED the files:
      * flags.txt: description of all the feature-control flags that are not
        structure members
      * test0.par: same as test.par, but with extfield
      * test-shwfs.i: call shwfs_test() with correct parameters. Just call
        it with yorick -i test-shwfs.i in examples/
      * test-extfield.i: test battery of extfield, check validity of results.
        Just call it with yorick -i test-extfield.i in examples/
      * test-all_v*: old version results of running test-all.i, catching up.

