commit ba060183935c9c7d5b5ae2b00da1ced4b2460778
Author: Francois Rigaut <frigaut@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:36:26 2014 +1000

    BUGFIX: when using no_reinit_wfs (in particular, this is the default when
    using the GUI), the wfs kernels do not get re-computed, and thus may
    be left with the imat kernel. Here, we force the re-init of the
    kernel in aoloop(), even if no_reinit_wfs is set.

commit 9c2e93e6a66ba92427dd75f6098ebfe3d9e5a803
Author: Francois Rigaut <frigaut@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 10:28:18 2014 +1000

    - Added feature: can now filter out Rayleigh-affected subapertures right from
    the start, i.e. within shwfs_init. The validsub are set to 0 if the subap
    is to be filtered, which means they will not even be in the imat.
    This is controlled through the use of the parameter "filter_rayleigh_sub".
    Set this parameter to a value between 0 and 1. A subaperture i with
    rayleigh_flux(i) / max(rayleigh_flux) above filter_rayleigh_sub will be
    filtered out. Useful for GeMS simulations

