commit dd336403478235334cc6a67a98dc21fbc6b02fd1
Author: Francois Rigaut <frigaut@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 19 15:53:11 2012 +1100

    Provide a mechanism to not pass pscreens in shared memory for svipc use.
    This caused some still-unresolved slow down in execution time. I
    suspect some conflict in accessing the shared memory between the
    (sometime) many threads. To be backward compatible, the default is
    still to pass pscreens through shared memory, but I provide a way to
    just replicate them in each threads (through natural behaviour of fork()).
    This can be done by setting the variable pscreens_no_shm.
    Two consequences if this is selected:
    - pscreens can not be changed on the fly, in particular, I'm not sure
    what happened in case of a swap.
    - the amount of RAM used is significantly larger, as pscreens are
    replicated across all threads.
    That said, it seems to fix the slow down problem. But the later mostly
    occured when dealing with big phase screens, so might not affect many users,
    thus I retain the old behaviour as default.

