commit 56fc3d9a0c55c4de419a3617e95867fa5ab9bf96
Author: Francois Rigaut <frigaut@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Oct 12 14:50:32 2012 +1100

    Bunch of changes to switch to a better version of the extended field
    method: now we put the result of the FFT for each "object" into a
    larger array, shifting them of necessary, before doing the convolution
    by the kernel(s), and then binning down. This allow proper treatment
    of the field stops and flux normalisation. It's fast too, although not
    much faster than the previous implementation.
    - bumped to 4.10.0
    - using wfs._nx to dimension arrays for yao_fast (kernel, mask, etc)
    - the roll is now done within _shwfs_phase2spots(), so suppressed a
      number of roll() calls ot prep arrays in yao_wfs.i
    - lots of changes in _shwfs_phase2spots(), including API changes
      (npb -> _nx). also added debug options, including writing out images
      on disk.
    - added spotpitch in agreement with new shwfs definitions (optional)
    - compatible with older parfiles. test parfiles run good.
    - had to move around sections within shwfs_init(), as kernel and mask
      definition now depend on the pixel size and extended field of view
      (_npixels and _nx). Probably need to clean up a little.

