commit f78fa7788b7348cbfc7ff355d29c7d9aed471e23
Author: Francois Rigaut <frigaut@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Sep 20 16:47:00 2012 +1000

    Do not pad small phaselet in fast shwfs C routine. The net effect
    is to be undersampled by a factor of 2 but might be ok if we are
    resampling anyway by a large factor. Tests show that it does not
    save an significant fraction of computation time (about 20-30%),
    so it might not be worth using this option. There are other complications,
    for instance it reduces the possibilities in final pixel size, as we
    start by a quantum pixel size which is twice what it is when phaselet
    is padded. To exercise this option, set no_pad_simage to 1.

commit 59c7f17064ca4ba2a7a2d7a263ce38dad28cbc47
Author: Francois Rigaut <frigaut@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Sep 20 15:13:43 2012 +1000

    Relatively big commit, mostly to save time and RAM for ELT systems:
    - added dm.use_def_of to replicate dm defs from one dm to another (e.g.
    when using disjointpup)
    - now use shared memory version of pscreens between parent and child (reduces
     RAM foorprint)
    - added no_reinit_wfs parameter to aoloop (time saving)
    - if no_ee is set, don't compute encircled_energy in after_loop() (time
    saving)

